For the first live album of His career, Italian rocker Ligabue Introduces a new band of three guitars, bass, drums, and most Significantly, no keyboards. A terrific live performer, this over 1997 double set, Ligabue revisits all of His best songs to date in electrified versions That almost invariably trump the studio ones. 
In Additions, up and down from a stage offers a choice few surprises, such as Mick Taylor 's guest appearance on "You have a moment God," and three previously unissued studio recordings: "The Day of Pain That one has," "Last Tango in Memphis, "and the would-be classic" Between Stage and Reality. "
